orking group on hydrogen energy is promoting the local application of hydrogen energy through pilot projects. As of October 2025, applications for 28 hydrogen energy pilot projects have been approved in principle, including hydrogen buses, hydrogen street washing vehicles, and the first public hydrogen refueling station. In mid-2024, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Government announced the \"Hong Kong Hydrogen Energy Development Strategy,\" proposing four major strategies: \"improving regulations,\" \"establishing standards,\" \"aligning with the market,\" and \"prudently advancing.\" This aims to create a favorable environment for local hydrogen energy development in a stable and orderly manner, while also expanding cooperation between Hong Kong and the Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area, and even globally, integrating Hong Kong into the overall national development strategy and developing new productive forces.","page":23,"modes":["Road"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":81591,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"General e-mobility measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"electrification of vehicles in airport restricted areas,","page":23,"modes":["Aviation"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":81591,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"EV charging infrastructure measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"the increase of electric vehicle charging stations,","page":23,"modes":["Aviation"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":81591,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Alternative fuels","purpose":"Promote alternative fuels","instrument":"Hydrogen support measures","